Just focus on libraries section and click right on any of it and select 'Find' (or just press ctrl+f)

The fucntion is not case sensitive.

 you can type the name of the table you need and specify in which library to look.

You can choose a specific library or all the libraries 

If you want to list all the tables of a library just type '*' and then select the library.

in the results list you can open the table, view columns and properties as usual. you can also view in excel.
with that function SAS will create an excel file. (if a warning appears then just click ok)

